THE SENATE
S.B. NO.
THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE. 2026
STATE OF HAWAII
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO DISCRIMINATION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that Hawaii has a strong,
2 historic commitment to civil rights. The legislature further
3 finds that the extension to the statute of limitations provided
4 by this Act would ensure that individuals in Hawaii have greater
5 access to civil-rights protections that reflect the community
6 values of the State: fairness, dignity, and inclusion. The
7 legislature also finds that this extension provides individuals
8 with a more reasonable timeframe to recognize, report, and seek
9 redress for unlawful discrimination under Hawaii state law.
10 The purpose of this Act is to extend the statute of
11 limitations for filing complaints with the Hawaii civil rights
12 commission to one year.
13 SECTION 2. Section 368-11, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
14 amended by amending subsection (c) to read as follows:
15 "(c) No complaint shall be filed after the expiration of
16 [one -hundred eighty dayo] one year after the date:
